President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate William LaPlante for Under Secretary for Acquisition and Sustainment at the Department of Defense. LaPlante is a seasoned national security leader with nearly four decades of experience in acquisition, technology, sustainment, and the defense industrial base. He is currently the president and CEO of Draper Laboratory, where he focuses on aligning the company's work with emerging technology and global competition. Prior to joining Draper, LaPlante served as senior vice president for the MITRE Corporation's National Sector, overseeing federally funded research and development centers for the Department of Defense and the Department of Commerce. He also served in the Obama-Biden Administration as the Assistant Secretary of the Air Force for Acquisition, Technology, and Logistics. LaPlante has been involved in various scientific boards and commissions focused on national security and has earned multiple degrees in engineering and applied physics.